WEBVTT

00:04:28.331 --> 00:04:31.362
to everyday people like the pig farmer,

00:04:31.386 --> 00:04:32.735
like you.

00:04:32.759 --> 00:04:35.343
I cofounded one of these companies.

00:04:35.367 --> 00:04:36.518
Three years ago,

00:04:36.542 --> 00:04:39.529
together with a fellow biologist
and friend of mine,

00:04:39.553 --> 00:04:41.133
Zeke Alvarez Saavedra,

00:04:41.157 --> 00:04:43.772
we decided to make personal DNA machines

00:04:43.796 --> 00:04:45.513
that anyone could use.

00:04:45.957 --> 00:04:49.535
Our goal was to bring DNA science
to more people in new places.

00:04:49.892 --> 00:04:52.053
We started working in our basements.

00:04:52.077 --> 00:04:54.130
We had a simple question:

00:04:54.154 --> 00:04:55.905
What could the world look like

00:04:55.929 --> 00:04:58.356
if everyone could analyze DNA?

00:04:58.380 --> 00:04:59.642
We were curious,